  "chapter": {
    "number": 37,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Elihu Proclaims God’s Majesty"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“At this my heart also pounds",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and leaps from its place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen closely to the thunder of His voice",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the rumbling that comes from His mouth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He unleashes His lightning beneath the whole sky",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and sends it to the ends of the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Then there comes a roaring sound;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He thunders with His majestic voice.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "He does not restrain the lightning",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when His voice resounds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "God thunders wondrously with His voice;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He does great things we cannot comprehend.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For He says to the snow, ‘Fall on the earth,’",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and to the gentle rain, ‘Pour out a mighty downpour.’",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He seals up the hand of every man,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "so that all men may know His work.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wild animals enter their lairs;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "they settle down in their dens.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The tempest comes from its chamber,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the cold from the driving north winds.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "By the breath of God the ice is formed",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the watery expanses are frozen.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He loads the clouds with moisture;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He scatters His lightning through them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "They swirl about,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "whirling at His direction,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "accomplishing all that He commands",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over the face of all the earth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whether for punishment or for His land,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He accomplishes this in His loving devotion.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Listen to this, O Job;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "stand still and consider the wonders of God.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you know how God dispatches the clouds",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "or makes the lightning flash?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Do you understand how the clouds float,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "those wonders of Him who is perfect in knowledge?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You whose clothes get hot",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the land lies hushed under the south wind,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "can you, like Him, spread out the skies",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to reflect the heat like a mirror of bronze?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Teach us what we should say to Him;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "we cannot draw up our case when our faces are in darkness.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Should He be told that I want to speak?",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "Would a man ask to be swallowed up",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 3208
          },
          {
            "text": "?",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Now no one can gaze at the sun",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when it is bright in the skies",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "after the wind has swept them clean.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Out of the north He comes in golden splendor;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "awesome majesty surrounds Him.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Almighty is beyond our reach;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He is exalted in power!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "In His justice and great righteousness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He does not oppress.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore, men fear Him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for He is not partial to the wise in heart.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 3208,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or speak without being swallowed up",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 37,
          "verse": 20
        }
      }
    ]
  },
